        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 2:29PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 229 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Japton, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Aurora...                         Wesley...
Huntsville...                     Dryfork...
Japton...                         Weathers...
Kingston...                       Witter...
Marble...                         Georgetown...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
